# Workspace Status — Implementation Plan

## Concept

Add a Linear-style workflow status to workspaces, separate from the existing `state` (lifecycle) column. Single `status` column with **sticky vs flow** semantics — no manual/derived split.

### Status Values

```
backlog → in-progress → in-review → done
                                     canceled
```

| Status | Type | Icon | Color | Auto-derive behavior |
|--------|------|------|-------|---------------------|
| `backlog` | Sticky | ○ (circle outline) | Gray | Only user can move it out |
| `in-progress` | Flow | ◐ (half-filled) | Yellow/Amber | Default. Auto-progresses to `in-review` on PR |
| `in-review` | Flow | ● (filled circle) | Purple | Auto-set when PR created. Auto-progresses to `done` on PR merge |
| `done` | Terminal | ✓ (checkmark) | Green | Auto-set on PR merge OR archive-with-commits |
| `canceled` | Sticky | ✕ (x mark) | Red/Gray | Only user can move it out |

### Relationship to Existing Columns

```
state:          "initializing" | "ready" | "archived" | "error"   ← KEEP (lifecycle)
status:         "backlog" | "in-progress" | "in-review" | "done" | "canceled"  ← NEW (workflow)
session_status: "idle" | "working" | "error" | "needs_response" | "needs_plan_response"  ← KEEP (agent activity)
```

- `state` = git worktree lifecycle (is the workspace usable?)
- `status` = workflow position (what phase is the work in?)
- `session_status` = real-time agent activity (is the agent busy right now?)

All three are orthogonal. A workspace can be `state=ready`, `status=in-review`, `session_status=working` (agent is doing follow-up work on a PR that's open).

### Auto-Derive Rules

| Event | Current Status | New Status | Condition |
|-------|---------------|------------|-----------|
| Workspace created | — | `in-progress` | Always (DB default) |
| PR created (`pr_url` set) | `in-progress` | `in-review` | Only if status is a flow state |
| PR merged (future) | `in-review` | `done` | Only if status is a flow state |
| Workspace archived | any | `done` | **Even sticky states** — archive is definitive |
| User manual override | any | any | Always allowed |

**Sticky rule**: When `status` is `backlog` or `canceled`, auto-derive events (PR created, etc.) do NOT change it. Only the user can move it out. Exception: archiving always sets `done`.

